<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06618</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING AN EPIDEMICS AND/OR PANDEMICS PREPAREDNESS PLAN, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to establish an epidemic/pandemic emergency plan in order for the country to be better prepared to recognize and manage future threats of epidemic/pandemic.
Proposes for an intensive nationwide information campaign on emerging/re-emerging infectious diseases to educate the people on its nature, causes, transmission and prevention.
Proposes the establishment of Endemic/Pandemic Emergency Council which shall: 
a) Identify isolation centers and health care facilities; 
b) Authorize quarantine of individuals or groups of individuals;
c) Purchase, store or distribute sufficiently adequate supply of PPEs, anti-viral agents, anti-toxins, serums and vaccines, and ensure that their use and rationing be controlled, restricted and regulated in the event of an epidemic/pandemic;
d) Establish a comprehensive monitoring program to determine the sufficiency and effectiveness of the programs and activities in preventing the spread of the disease;
e) Establish reporting procedures that will ensure the confidentiality and non-disclosure of the personal information gathered and medical records of all patients and individuals infected or suspected to have been infected with the disease;
f) Provide health care workers and responders with adequate PPEs like N95 respiratory masks, gloves, face shields and goggles.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SY-ALVARADO, &quot;KUYA&quot; JOSE ANTONIO R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-03-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON DEFEAT COVID-19 AD-HOC COMMITTEE ON 2020-05-04</td></tr></table>